# Privacy Policy

**Effective date:** 04/15/2026

## 1. Who We Are
Tabulus is an iOS app built and operated by Robert Fusting, a solo developer.  
**Contact:** robertmfusting@gmail.com

## 2. Information We Collect

### You Provide Directly:
- **Account:** username, email, password (email signup) — or Apple ID and optional email (Sign in with Apple)
- **Profile:** optional profile image
- **Content you post:** reviews, ratings, game night entries (games played, participants, outcomes), photos (up to 5 per upload, 8MB each)
- **Social graph:** friend requests you send/accept
- **Reports:** reports you submit on other users' content

### Collected Automatically:
- Authentication tokens (so you stay signed in)
- Server logs (IP address, timestamps, request paths) are used for real-time debugging only and are not retained

**We do NOT collect:** location, contacts, analytics, crash reports, advertising identifiers, or any third-party tracking.

## 3. How We Use It
- Operate the app (accounts, posting, feeds, friends)
- Authenticate you and keep you signed in
- Send password reset emails
- Enforce our rules (responding to reports)
- Secure the service (abuse prevention, debugging)

## 4. How It’s Stored
- Backend hosted on Microsoft Azure (Azure Container Apps, West US 2 region)
- Images stored in Azure Blob Storage; served via short-lived signed URLs
- Passwords are hashed with argon2; we never store them in plaintext
- Refresh tokens are stored in the iOS Keychain on your device

## 5. Third Parties
We share data only with infrastructure providers needed to run the app:

- **Microsoft Azure** — hosting, database, image storage, and transactional email (Azure Communication Services) for password resets  
- **Apple** — if you use Sign in with Apple, Apple handles that authentication  
- **BoardGameGeek** — game metadata is fetched by our server; BGG does not receive any information about you  

We do not sell or share your data for advertising. We do not use analytics or tracking SDKs.

## 6. Your Choices and Rights
- Only friends can view your game nights. Friends can be removed from the Friends tab on your profile page; once removed, neither user can view the other's game night content.
- Block users to remove them as friends and stop seeing game night and review content that they post.
- Edit your profile in the app
- Delete game nights via the ellipsis menu on any game night card
- Delete reviews via the delete button on the associated board game page
- Delete your account in the app (**Settings → Delete Account**) — this permanently removes your account and all associated content from our systems
- **Access/export:** email robertmfusting@gmail.com
- Password reset via the forgot-password flow on the app login page

## 7. Content Moderation
- Game Nights and Reviews have a clickable ellipsis button on the top right corner that when clicked will prompt the user to report the content or block the user.
- Users will no longer see any content posted by a user that they have blocked.
- Users will no longer see any content they have reported.
- Any content with 3 or more reports is subject to be removed.
- Reports are checked manually by Robert Fusting every 24 hours.


## 8. Children
Tabulus is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.  
If you believe a child has created an account, email robertmfusting@gmail.com and we will remove it.

## 9. Data Retention
We keep your data while your account is active.  
When you delete your account, we remove your profile, reviews, game nights, and uploaded images from our live systems.  
Deleted data may persist in encrypted database backups for up to 7 days before being automatically purged.

## 10. Security
We use HTTPS for all network traffic, hashed passwords, token-based authentication, and platform-provided secure storage (iOS Keychain). However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure. While we strive to use commercially reasonable means to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

## 11. Changes
We may update this policy. Material changes will be posted here with a new effective date.

